data.Name: NSLOCTEXT("[614BA4C59907924257CAFBE0BB7DFECA]", "DDACADFA483114D9E18661AEA375EFEF", "Devannos Shrine")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[614BA4C59907924257CAFBE0BB7DFECA]", "651213D04E845DEB21CE4FBB9E89C9E0", "Devannos is the god of war and hunting, guiding both warriors and hunters with his divine precision. His influence ensures arrows fly true and battles are won in his honor. According to legend, Devannos taught the first hunters how to track and take down prey, his guidance so precise that even novices could not miss. He is said to have intervened in the Battle of Bloodfields, guiding arrows to secure victory for his favored warriors. Some believe Devannos walks among mortals as a silent archer, testing skills and rewarding the worthy.")

data.Name: NSLOCTEXT("[9FDD392439DAC28A2C030390091F6DBE]", "866BFC01462498D3EE161B9F6B25EC0D", "Erdana Shrine")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[9FDD392439DAC28A2C030390091F6DBE]", "C13E5DAC4A1CA8B1A73E009B38F2D73B", "Erdana, the Earth Mother, embodies the nurturing and sustaining aspects of nature. She is revered as the source of fertility, growth, and prosperity, with her influence felt in every harvest and blooming flower. Erdana is believed to share in the sufferings of her people, feeling their pain during droughts and famines. Her laughter is said to be heard in the rustling of leaves and bubbling of brooks, bringing good fortune to those who listen. Legends tell of Erdana gifting humanity with agricultural knowledge, ensuring her children would never go hungry.")

data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[B711FED74C55F94D80892ED280262DAE]", "D0A39B924D994640A384BFA60B906741", "Kranek, the harbinger of death, claims the souls of the deceased, carrying them to the afterlife.")

data.Name: NSLOCTEXT("[807D0801DAD3AC9FD75833E8623882DD]", "9590EE204236766A9B5D179370E921CB", "Morvathis Shrine")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[807D0801DAD3AC9FD75833E8623882DD]", "9752C75D47F493E91916E9A954FBA9CC", "Morvathis, represents the primordial void and the deepest, most unfathomable aspects of existence. As a fundamental force of creation and destruction, Morvathis embodies the concept of endless potential and the unknown. This deity is associated with the depths of the earth and the mysteries of death, but also with the emergence of new life and order from seeming nothingness. Morvathis is often depicted as an ever-changing, formless entity, reflecting the unpredictable nature of the cosmos.")

data.Name: NSLOCTEXT("[DB0CEED9AE8603FB96A233F00ECAB856]", "383C038244E75B4253FD77941C632AB7", "Veylnor Shrine")
data.Description: NSLOCTEXT("[DB0CEED9AE8603FB96A233F00ECAB856]", "36C2B8244B35CF94D923328EACE0027C", "Veylnor, is a deity shrouded in darkness and mystery, embodying the depths of night and the unseen forces that govern fate. This primordial god exists in the shadows, influencing events from behind a veil of obscurity. Veylnor\'s presence is felt in moments of uncertainty and introspection, guiding those who dare to seek truth in darkness. Legends speak of his ability to weave destinies, granting insight or confusion to those who invoke his name.
